A BILL
for
1 AN ACT relating to property taxation; specifying that if
2 multiple property tax exemptions apply to the same property
3 the exemptions shall be applied in the manner determined by
4 the department of revenue; specifying requirements for the
5 order of application of exemptions; and providing for an
6 effective date.
7
8 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Wyoming:
9
10 Section 1. W.S. 39-11-105 by creating a new
11 subsection (c) is amended to read:
12
13 39-11-105. Exemptions.
14
1 HB0279

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0709
1 (c) For any property where more than one (1)
2 exemption applies under subsection (a) of this section, the
3 exemptions shall be applied in a manner determined by the
4 department of revenue in accordance with the following:
5
6 (i) If the exemption is to a portion of the
7 assessed value of the property, the exemptions shall be
8 applied in sequence so that subsequent exemptions are
9 applied to the assessed value as it is modified by the
10 application of the preceding exemption;
11
12 (ii) Exemptions based on a percentage of
13 property value shall be applied in the order of the
14 smallest percentage to the largest percentage;
15
16 (iii) Exemptions not based on a percentage of
17 property value shall be applied after any exemptions that
18 are based on a percentage of property value.
